$AAPL Q4 2020 Earnings Preview

Apple (NASDAQ:AAPL) is scheduled to announce Q4 earnings results on Thursday, October 29th, after market close.

The consensus EPS Estimate is $0.70 and the consensus Revenue Estimate is $63.33B (-1.1% Y/Y).

Over the last 2 years, AAPL has beaten EPS estimates 100% of the time and has beaten revenue estimates 100% of the time.

Analyst expects iPhone revenue of $27.73B; iPad $6.14B, Services revenue of $14.12B.

Analyst expects gross margin of 38.1%.

Over the last 3 months, EPS estimates have seen 21 upward revisions and 11 downward. Revenue estimates have seen 22 upward revisions and 7 downward.

links.title: Apple working on its own search engine as Google ties could be cut soon
links.description: Apple is said to be working on its own search engine to replace Google. As of now Google pays Apple between $10b and $12b a year to be the main search provider on Apple devices, but that deal will soon expire and a reported antitrust case against Google by the US Department of Justice could prevent its extension.
